question:
District category contains University Campus, Academic District, Automotive District, and Archaeological District.
Supermarkets category contains Dollar General, Aldi (Germany), and SuperValu.
Product category contains Half-and-half, Croissants, and Granola Bars.
The number of each University Campus 's SuperValu equals the difference of each University Campus 's Aldi (Germany) and each Automotive District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Archaeological District 's Dollar General equals 13.
The number of each University Campus 's Aldi (Germany) equals 7.
The number of each Aldi (Germany) 's Croissants equals 1 more than the sum of each Aldi (Germany) 's Granola Bars and each SuperValu 's Croissants.
The number of each Aldi (Germany) 's Granola Bars equals 20 more than each SuperValu 's Croissants.
The number of each University Campus 's Dollar General equals 6 times each Automotive District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each SuperValu 's Granola Bars equals each Academic District 's Aldi (Germany).
The number of each Academic District 's Aldi (Germany) equals each Aldi (Germany) 's Croissants.
The number of each Academic District 's Dollar General equals 5.
The number of each Archaeological District 's SuperValu equals 8 times the sum of each Aldi (Germany) 's Croissants, each SuperValu 's Croissants, and each Aldi (Germany) 's Granola Bars.
The number of each Automotive District 's Dollar General equals 22 times each Automotive District 's Aldi (Germany).
The number of each Dollar General 's Croissants equals 3 times each Automotive District 's Dollar General.
The number of each Automotive District 's Aldi (Germany) equals 20.
The number of each SuperValu 's Croissants equals 12.
How many Supermarkets does University Campus have?
solution:
Define each Automotive District 's Aldi (Germany) as R; So R = 20.
Define each Automotive District 's Dollar General as r; So r = 22 * R = 22 * 20 = 3.
Define each Automotive District 's Supermarkets as a; So a = r + R = 3 + 20 = 0.
Define each University Campus 's Dollar General as l; So l = 6 * a = 6 * 0 = 0.
Define each University Campus 's Aldi (Germany) as n; So n = 7.
Define each University Campus 's SuperValu as D; So D = n - a = 7 - 0 = 7.
Define each University Campus 's Supermarkets as h; b = D + l = 7 + 0 = 7; So h = n + b = 7 + 7 = 14.
